727435f-b.title: Queens: Metropolitan Avenue - Union Turnpike
727435f-b.text:
Metropolitan Avenue, (tracks thereon) at the N.E. corner of
Union Turnpike, showing in two views the Autenrieth's Hotel,
also known as Alberts IInn in 1923, and Utopian Inn in 1929. A
section of this hotel is in the new proposed line of the Turnpike.
October 1923
Views 1 and 2
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection
MAY BE REPRODUCED.

727410f-b.title: Queens: Metropolitan Avenue - 75th Road
727410f-b.text:
Metropolitan Avenue (tracks thereon) at the N.W. corner of
7Sth Road, showing in two views the James Nendrickson house; erected
on the site of the Townsend Hendricksen house (1852) which burned
down. This place in 1909 was owree 'b Japes Van Sicklen. Later
it was occupied bv a Tennis Club 'Swhdche- hwd the house moved to
the south side of Metropolitan Avenue and remodeled. In 1929 it
was on the S.E. corner of Metropolitan Avenue and 72nd Road. IIt
has,since a fire, been altered and is now a two family house.
October 1923
Views 1 and 2
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection
